{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"## What\nProve the batch write reduces commit count and does not break crash-resume: a before/after\ncommit-count benchmark on a synthetic many-event import, plus rollback + crash-resume tests.\n**Depends on B1 (890d) and B2 (6386)** — the primitive and the importer adoption must exist.\n\n## Why\nBatching changes commit granularity (N events per commit). We must demonstrate the win\n(commit-count reduction) and prove the safety properties: all-or-nothing per commit, and\nthat a crash mid-batch plus the `source_id` re-scan resumes cleanly. NOTE: the importer's\nexisting LINE parsing is fail-open (a malformed NDJSON line is skipped); the whole-chunk\nrollback proven here is a property of the BATCH PRIMITIVE (`batch_stage_and_commit`) — one\nevent that fails validation inside a chunk rolls back that chunk's already-staged events —\nnot of the importer's line parser.\n\n## Scope\n- Benchmark test: build a synthetic N-event NDJSON (N>=2560), run `import_tickets`, assert\n  `git rev-list --count HEAD` on the tracker == `ceil(N/256)` (>=10x fewer commits than the\n  per-event path which is ~N).\n- Malformed-event-mid-chunk test (batch primitive level): a chunk containing one event that\n  fails `_validate_event` triggers whole-chunk rollback — index clean, no partial commit,\n  no phantom staged blob.\n- Crash-resume test: simulate a crash before a chunk's `git commit` (e.g. monkeypatch the\n  commit to raise after staging); assert the store is left whole-commit-or-none, then re-run\n  the import and assert the `source_id` re-scan skips committed events and re-emits the rest.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Benchmark test asserts tracker commit count == `ceil(N/256)` on a synthetic N-event import (N>=2560), i.e. >=10x fewer commits than per-event\n- [ ] Malformed-event-mid-chunk test proves the batch primitive rolls the whole chunk back (index clean via `git diff --cached --name-only` empty, no partial commit)\n- [ ] Crash-resume test proves partial-batch recovery leaves whole-commit-or-none and a re-run's source_id re-scan resumes cleanly (no duplicate/lost events)\n- [ ] Regression suites named + green: `tests/unit/test_store_batch_write.py`, replay/dedup/union-merge convergence tests, SNAPSHOT compaction tests\n- [ ] `make test` green"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783650813811178001,"uuid":"a0a687a6-fb0c-4385-a71d-6fa0a210dafb"}